	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Good to see that you where able to make it.  
<br />
<br />Regarding the pins in the way, next time, since you now have more experience in modding, you should try to cut the traces instead. This is more risky but now you have experience in making a repro and know where to connect wires so the risk should be lower. This way you won't have the pin issue.  
<br />
<br />In my case I don't really mind since I use the cart for dev use only and with a famicom I don't have to open the main unit, just put the cart directly.
<br />
<br />Good luck on your next repro <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


